{
  "doc_id": "19314",
  "text": "The media used were Luria-Bertani (LB), King's-B (KB) (Schaad et al., 2001 ) and AB minimal medium, which was supplemented when necessary with 2% mannitol [CITATION_1] or with cycloheximide (50 µg l -1 ). The bacteria were grown at 27 °C, except for biosensors and P. atrosepticum SM1, which were grown at 28 and 25°C respectively. All AHLs standard that used in this study were purchased from Sigma (Sigma-Aldrich, Inc., St. Louis, Mo., USA).",
